1
00:00:00,567 --> 00:00:01,433
<i> Hello, Philippines!</i>

2
00:00:01,433 --> 00:00:03,000
<i> And hello, world!</i>

3
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:05,800
<i> Alright! Welcome to Hotel 88!</i>

4
00:00:05,800 --> 00:00:06,933
<i> Welcome, sir.</i>

5
00:00:06,933 --> 00:00:08,567
<i> We only have one guest,</i>

6
00:00:08,567 --> 00:00:10,100
<i> and you're suspecting him?</i>

7
00:00:10,100 --> 00:00:12,067
<i> I wouldn't suspect him</i>

8
00:00:12,067 --> 00:00:14,600
<i>if he wasn't trying
to open Papa's room.</i>

9
00:00:14,600 --> 00:00:15,933
<i>The 50 million
is nowhere to be found</i>

10
00:00:15,933 --> 00:00:19,600
<i>and the hotel owes the bank
money that you need to pay.</i>

11
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:23,967
Papa agreed to give the Almazans
<i> a share of this hotel for free?</i>

12
00:00:23,967 --> 00:00:26,000
<i>That means he
was a generous friend.</i>

13
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:27,400
<i> So what?</i>

14
00:00:27,400 --> 00:00:29,000
<i> Why would he shoot Uncle Fred</i>

15
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:30,733
if he agreed to share the hotel
<i> in the first place?</i>

16
00:00:30,733 --> 00:00:31,933
<i>Where did you put
the money, huh?</i>

17
00:00:31,933 --> 00:00:33,167
<i>We don't even know
he convinced Papa</i>

18
00:00:33,167 --> 00:00:35,767
<i>to give him shares without
getting anything in return.</i>

19
00:00:35,800 --> 00:00:38,533
<i>For sure Uncle Mike
had a reason to agree.</i>

20
00:00:38,533 --> 00:00:43,000
<i>We need a general manager
to lead this hotel's operations.</i>

21
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:44,433
<i> We want things to be fair?</i>

22
00:00:44,433 --> 00:00:45,433
<i> Let's vote on it.</i>

23
00:00:50,800 --> 00:00:52,333
There are four of them
and only three of us,

24
00:00:52,333 --> 00:00:53,533
and you agreed to vote on it?

25
00:00:53,533 --> 00:00:55,600
Are you sure
he'll take your side?

26
00:00:57,767 --> 00:00:59,333
You shouldn't have agreed to it.

27
00:00:59,333 --> 00:01:01,833
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

28
00:01:01,833 --> 00:01:03,600
[GIO] Aren't you worried?

29
00:01:04,033 --> 00:01:04,967
Nope.

30
00:01:05,967 --> 00:01:07,700
Jeez, Martin.

31
00:01:07,733 --> 00:01:09,367
I'll say it again, okay?

32
00:01:09,367 --> 00:01:10,833
There are four of them
and only three of us.

33
00:01:10,833 --> 00:01:12,500
Leon will vote for me.

34
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:13,833
That's some intense
fighting spirit.

35
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:17,800
Are you sure
he'll take your side?

36
00:01:18,667 --> 00:01:19,633
Our side.

37
00:01:19,967 --> 00:01:21,667
He'll take our side.

38
00:01:21,667 --> 00:01:24,000
Leon is my friend,
and I know him.

39
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:25,533
He wouldn't suggest
having a vote

40
00:01:25,533 --> 00:01:26,967
if he wasn't going
to vote for me.

41
00:01:27,800 --> 00:01:28,867
I don't know.

42
00:01:29,633 --> 00:01:30,833
I still don't trust him.

43
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:33,100
I will be the GM of the hotel.

44
00:01:33,967 --> 00:01:35,633
I'm better than Luna,

45
00:01:35,633 --> 00:01:37,800
and running a business
is my strength.

46
00:01:38,733 --> 00:01:41,000
So my friend
would vote for me.

47
00:01:42,500 --> 00:01:44,533
[SCOFFS] I hope so.

48
00:01:44,533 --> 00:01:51,167
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

49
00:02:00,833 --> 00:02:07,667
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

50
00:03:07,467 --> 00:03:09,900
Your brothers seem skeptical.

51
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:12,067
I can't blame them.

52
00:03:12,833 --> 00:03:14,233
Don't worry, bro.

53
00:03:14,233 --> 00:03:15,700
I've explained it to them.

54
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:19,200
I know you're
the best person for the job.

55
00:03:19,767 --> 00:03:20,900
I know you.

56
00:03:22,267 --> 00:03:25,500
I know your dedication
to these things.

57
00:03:26,767 --> 00:03:30,133
You know, my siblings
are just worried.

58
00:03:30,933 --> 00:03:33,467
Of course, they think
you'll vote for your sister.

59
00:03:33,933 --> 00:03:34,967
She's your sister, after all.

60
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:38,700
You know the hotel
better than we do.

61
00:03:38,700 --> 00:03:40,300
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

62
00:03:40,300 --> 00:03:41,767
I need this.

63
00:03:42,967 --> 00:03:44,033
I know.

64
00:03:44,033 --> 00:03:48,800
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

65
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:50,167
[MUSIC FADES]

66
00:03:52,633 --> 00:03:59,567
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

67
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,000
[SIGHS]

68
00:04:11,167 --> 00:04:12,900
Dad didn't give me
the opportunity

69
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:14,600
to save my business
in Manila.

70
00:04:15,633 --> 00:04:19,667
I don't want to fail
with this hotel this time, Leon.

71
00:04:21,167 --> 00:04:24,000
You want to show your stepfather
that you can do it

72
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,667
without his help?

73
00:04:25,667 --> 00:04:27,000
I will do everything I can

74
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:30,900
to save the property
that our fathers left us.

75
00:04:30,933 --> 00:04:32,800
And I know it
won't be easy.

76
00:04:33,867 --> 00:04:35,067
But knowing you,

77
00:04:35,667 --> 00:04:37,533
you'd never give up
no matter how hard it is.

78
00:04:40,067 --> 00:04:41,833
Thank you for your trust, Leon.

79
00:04:42,233 --> 00:04:43,700
Don't worry, bro.

80
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:46,267
Even though I'm busy with
the businesses Dad left behind,

81
00:04:46,267 --> 00:04:49,333
I'll support you
with the help you need.

82
00:04:50,067 --> 00:04:52,100
You have to be the GM.

83
00:04:52,100 --> 00:04:53,133
Thank you.

84
00:04:55,067 --> 00:04:56,533
[LUNA] Can we talk?

85
00:04:57,033 --> 00:04:57,967
Nope.

86
00:04:59,167 --> 00:05:01,067
Sell me your share.

87
00:05:02,233 --> 00:05:03,300
Out of the three of you,

88
00:05:03,300 --> 00:05:05,700
I know you're the one
who needs money the most.

89
00:05:06,733 --> 00:05:07,733
Are you sure?

90
00:05:08,867 --> 00:05:09,900
Why?

91
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:12,033
What do you know about me?

92
00:05:13,233 --> 00:05:14,200
I know you.

93
00:05:14,900 --> 00:05:16,067
You're practical.

94
00:05:17,100 --> 00:05:18,200
[SCOFFS]

95
00:05:19,300 --> 00:05:20,700
I'm practical?

96
00:05:22,367 --> 00:05:24,967
You talk like we're close.

97
00:05:24,967 --> 00:05:31,900
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

98
00:05:31,900 --> 00:05:32,900
Why?

99
00:05:35,967 --> 00:05:37,100
Are we close?

100
00:05:46,767 --> 00:05:47,733
Gio, please.

101
00:05:49,267 --> 00:05:50,700
This isn't the time.

102
00:05:51,100 --> 00:05:52,300
When is the right time?

103
00:05:55,267 --> 00:05:57,967
We'll both benefit
if you sell to me.

104
00:05:58,933 --> 00:06:01,867
You only remember me when
it's convenient for you, huh?

105
00:06:02,633 --> 00:06:04,933
You remember I exist
whenever you need me.

106
00:06:04,933 --> 00:06:11,900
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

107
00:06:11,933 --> 00:06:12,933
You're right.

108
00:06:15,667 --> 00:06:17,000
I need money.

109
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:25,100
But who said I want
to work with you?

110
00:06:37,433 --> 00:06:38,867
Have some snacks.

111
00:06:38,867 --> 00:06:42,700
Thank you, Monette, but you
really don't have to serve me.

112
00:06:42,733 --> 00:06:44,133
[MONETTE]
Oh, please. It's okay.

113
00:06:44,867 --> 00:06:48,833
I also gave your brothers
some drinks to cool down.

114
00:06:48,833 --> 00:06:53,100
It seems seeing the Almazans
make their blood boil.

115
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:54,800
Here.

116
00:06:55,300 --> 00:06:56,167
Oh.

117
00:06:56,167 --> 00:06:58,900
Do they make your blood
boil now too?

118
00:06:58,900 --> 00:07:00,800
[INHALES DEEPLY]
It's not like that.

119
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:02,433
I was just thinking
about my dad.

120
00:07:03,233 --> 00:07:06,267
He and Uncle Fred were on good
terms before they died, right?

121
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:10,067
Yeah, but he was
angry when he left, wasn't he?

122
00:07:10,067 --> 00:07:11,367
I was here.

123
00:07:12,133 --> 00:07:15,467
Maybe he was just drunk
so you thought he was angry.

124
00:07:17,233 --> 00:07:20,967
Possibly. Why?
Is something bothering you?

125
00:07:21,367 --> 00:07:24,733
You see, Papa agreed to share
this hotel with Uncle Fred

126
00:07:24,733 --> 00:07:26,767
without getting anything
in return.

127
00:07:26,767 --> 00:07:29,467
Would you trust a friend
that much?

128
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:32,467
What's your point?

129
00:07:33,933 --> 00:07:36,400
If you really
trusted each other,

130
00:07:37,033 --> 00:07:38,400
would you kill each other?

131
00:07:39,033 --> 00:07:42,867
So you think
they didn't kill each other?

132
00:07:42,867 --> 00:07:44,867
Possibly.

133
00:07:44,867 --> 00:07:46,167
What if they didn't?

134
00:07:46,733 --> 00:07:48,500
Well, if that's the case,

135
00:07:48,533 --> 00:07:51,100
someone else killed them.
Is that right?

136
00:07:52,067 --> 00:07:53,400
I don't know, Monette.

137
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:58,000
But I still can't believe
they killed each other.

138
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:00,967
They've known each other
for years, so why now?

139
00:08:00,967 --> 00:08:07,900
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

140
00:08:11,067 --> 00:08:14,033
- [SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]
- [WIND CHIMES CHIMING]

141
00:08:14,033 --> 00:08:16,100
[LUNA]
Before we meet with them,

142
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:18,167
I want to have everything
in this memorized.

143
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:21,100
Luna.

144
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:26,800
You know I only want
what's best for you siblings.

145
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:28,133
[LUNA]
Of course, Ma.

146
00:08:29,233 --> 00:08:30,467
Why?

147
00:08:32,833 --> 00:08:39,800
Because, sweetheart,
if this partnership...

148
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:42,933
and running the hotel
is just going to cause problems,

149
00:08:42,933 --> 00:08:47,500
it's okay if
you don't push yourselves.

150
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:50,600
It's okay if you choose
a quieter life.

151
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:53,900
Ma, we're used to
business stress.

152
00:08:53,900 --> 00:08:55,033
I can handle this.

153
00:08:56,333 --> 00:08:59,633
The real headache
is Uncle Mike's kids.

154
00:08:59,633 --> 00:09:02,633
If I could just remove them
from their positions...

155
00:09:02,633 --> 00:09:04,367
Don't say that.

156
00:09:04,367 --> 00:09:06,833
But it's true, Ma.

157
00:09:06,833 --> 00:09:08,167
Like,
do they have any misconduct

158
00:09:08,167 --> 00:09:11,167
listed in this agreement?

159
00:09:11,167 --> 00:09:12,433
Misconduct?

160
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:17,133
Theft.
Embezzlement of funds.

161
00:09:17,133 --> 00:09:19,467
So we can strip them
of their ownership in the hotel.

162
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,567
Then that would be great.

163
00:09:27,133 --> 00:09:31,100
It's just...
this might take a while, Ma.

164
00:09:31,133 --> 00:09:32,967
Why?

165
00:09:32,967 --> 00:09:35,333
I didn't expect...

166
00:09:35,333 --> 00:09:39,167
there'd be complications
with the hotel Papa left behind.

167
00:09:39,167 --> 00:09:41,300
So we're still working on it.

168
00:09:41,300 --> 00:09:43,333
[LOUISE]<i> Can you pause
</i> for a while?

169
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:45,000
I mean...

170
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:47,000
So much has happened to you.

171
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:52,200
The bookstore closing...
Your father's death.

172
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:54,300
<i>You need time
for yourself.</i>

173
00:09:55,967 --> 00:09:58,500
<i>You haven't even had
the chance to grieve yet.</i>

174
00:10:00,167 --> 00:10:03,967
Martin, are you listening to me?

175
00:10:07,033 --> 00:10:08,367
Yes, Ma.

176
00:10:08,367 --> 00:10:09,900
I need to do this.

177
00:10:11,033 --> 00:10:13,367
Son, we have a lawyer

178
00:10:13,367 --> 00:10:16,033
who can act as
your representative there.

179
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:19,333
And the hotel
affairs can wait.

180
00:10:19,333 --> 00:10:23,933
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

181
00:10:23,933 --> 00:10:26,900
<i>Come home first,
to your family.</i>

182
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:29,300
No.

183
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:31,867
[LOUISE] No?

184
00:10:32,667 --> 00:10:34,300
You don't want to come home?

185
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:37,933
I'll stay here for now, Ma.

186
00:10:37,933 --> 00:10:39,700
I'll be fine.

187
00:10:39,700 --> 00:10:41,100
[LOUISE]
<i> Okay.</i>

188
00:10:42,067 --> 00:10:43,400
I'll let you be.

189
00:10:45,233 --> 00:10:47,033
Just be safe.

190
00:10:47,033 --> 00:10:48,567
Please?

191
00:10:48,567 --> 00:10:50,433
Okay, Ma. Bye.

192
00:10:52,233 --> 00:10:53,267
[PHONE BEEPS]

193
00:10:55,233 --> 00:11:02,100
[MYSTERIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

194
00:11:18,267 --> 00:11:19,600
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

195
00:11:21,567 --> 00:11:24,567
<i> It's my fault.</i>

196
00:11:24,567 --> 00:11:27,433
<i> It's my fault they died.</i>

197
00:11:27,433 --> 00:11:29,267
[BREATH QUIVERS]

198
00:11:31,567 --> 00:11:34,133
[BREATHING SHARPLY]

199
00:11:34,133 --> 00:11:40,400
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

200
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:42,100
[INHALES SHARPLY]

201
00:11:44,333 --> 00:11:51,233
[MUSIC BECOMES DARK]

202
00:11:52,433 --> 00:11:53,467
<i> No!</i>

203
00:11:54,667 --> 00:11:56,100
<i> Fred...</i>

204
00:11:56,100 --> 00:11:58,500
[PANICKED BREATHING]

205
00:11:58,500 --> 00:12:02,133
<i> Fred... Fred, no! No! No!</i>

206
00:12:02,133 --> 00:12:05,300
- Mama! Ma. Ma. Ma..
- No! [PANTING]

207
00:12:05,300 --> 00:12:06,600
Are you okay?

208
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:09,733
You were having a nightmare.

209
00:12:11,467 --> 00:12:13,233
You were calling their names.

210
00:12:14,300 --> 00:12:16,200
Who?

211
00:12:16,233 --> 00:12:17,800
Daddy and Uncle Mike.

212
00:12:20,467 --> 00:12:22,367
Are you okay?

213
00:12:25,500 --> 00:12:28,500
Go on, get some rest.
I'll follow in a bit.

214
00:12:28,500 --> 00:12:31,033
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

215
00:12:31,033 --> 00:12:33,300
Get some rest, Ma, okay?

216
00:12:39,467 --> 00:12:44,067
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

217
00:12:44,067 --> 00:12:45,633
[EXHALES]

218
00:12:48,067 --> 00:12:50,400
[RAPHIE HUMMING]

219
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:55,133
Good morning Philippines!
Good morning, Sir Jeff!

220
00:12:56,533 --> 00:12:57,667
Sir Jeff?

221
00:12:58,700 --> 00:13:01,367
[KNOCKING]

222
00:13:01,367 --> 00:13:02,667
Sir Jeff?

223
00:13:04,367 --> 00:13:07,533
[MONETTE] What did he say?
Is he having breakfast?

224
00:13:07,533 --> 00:13:09,400
He said to get
his breakfast ready.

225
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:11,533
He's not responding.

226
00:13:11,533 --> 00:13:13,633
Maybe you're just
knocking too sweetly again.

227
00:13:14,700 --> 00:13:16,500
[CLEARS THROAT, KNOCKS]

228
00:13:16,500 --> 00:13:19,733
Good morning, Sir Jeff!
Breakfast is ready!

229
00:13:21,467 --> 00:13:22,767
Still nothing.

230
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:28,833
Maybe Sir Jeff just
sleeps like a log.

231
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:31,533
Let's just leave him for now.

232
00:13:34,633 --> 00:13:38,467
- [KNOCKING]
- [BOTH GIGGLING]

233
00:13:38,467 --> 00:13:40,133
[CHAIR CREAKS]

234
00:13:40,133 --> 00:13:41,467
This is really messed up!

235
00:13:41,467 --> 00:13:42,600
Our dad gets killed,

236
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:45,200
they contributed nothing
to the hotel, and then what?

237
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:47,267
They're voting
on who gets to manage it.

238
00:13:47,267 --> 00:13:49,867
From their POV,
Papa fired the first shot.

239
00:13:49,867 --> 00:13:51,400
so they're furious too.

240
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:53,133
[MARTIN]
Don't worry.

241
00:13:53,133 --> 00:13:55,200
I'll be the GM
(General Manager).

242
00:13:55,233 --> 00:13:57,300
Oh, here we go again.

243
00:13:57,300 --> 00:13:58,833
You really believe Leon?

244
00:13:58,833 --> 00:14:01,900
That what? That Leon will
give his vote to Martin?

245
00:14:01,900 --> 00:14:03,133
Yes!

246
00:14:03,933 --> 00:14:05,733
That's a long shot.

247
00:14:05,733 --> 00:14:09,733
Even if you're his friend,
your opponent is his sibling.

248
00:14:09,733 --> 00:14:10,933
His own blood.

249
00:14:10,933 --> 00:14:13,333
I trust Leon.

250
00:14:13,333 --> 00:14:15,400
He knows how to honor a deal.

251
00:14:21,433 --> 00:14:23,567
You're voting for me though,
right, Leon?

252
00:14:23,567 --> 00:14:30,400
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

253
00:14:30,433 --> 00:14:32,300
I know Martin's
your best friend.

254
00:14:34,533 --> 00:14:36,167
But I'm your sister.

255
00:14:37,367 --> 00:14:38,467
Luna.

256
00:14:38,467 --> 00:14:40,467
If this were just
a simple family partnership,

257
00:14:40,467 --> 00:14:43,333
I wouldn't want to be
the hotel's GM.

258
00:14:43,333 --> 00:14:45,167
I'm doing this for Dad.

259
00:14:45,167 --> 00:14:51,833
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

260
00:14:56,267 --> 00:14:58,467
[LUNA]
For justice for his death.

261
00:14:58,467 --> 00:15:05,333
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

262
00:15:12,033 --> 00:15:13,133
[FRIDA] Jade?

263
00:15:13,133 --> 00:15:15,733
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

264
00:15:15,733 --> 00:15:20,533
Jade, do you want to go with me
to your favorite bookstore?

265
00:15:20,533 --> 00:15:23,967
[WATER RUSHING]

266
00:15:23,967 --> 00:15:26,633
My siblings and I
are going to Hotel 88.

267
00:15:26,633 --> 00:15:31,633
How about later?
We can go when you arrive home.

268
00:15:32,733 --> 00:15:36,367
I just want us
to spend more time together.

269
00:15:36,400 --> 00:15:37,800
- [PAINTBRUSH CLANGS]
- Well, I don't.

270
00:15:38,833 --> 00:15:39,833
Jade.

271
00:15:41,667 --> 00:15:43,033
Stop it, Mom.

272
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:46,400
What is this, huh? A bribe?

273
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:48,167
[FRIDA SIGHS]

274
00:15:48,167 --> 00:15:49,400
No.

275
00:15:49,867 --> 00:15:52,967
Can't I spend time
with my daughter?

276
00:15:53,667 --> 00:15:55,833
I know what you did, Mom.

277
00:15:56,833 --> 00:15:57,933
What did I do?

278
00:15:57,933 --> 00:15:59,833
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

279
00:15:59,833 --> 00:16:00,833
[JUSTIN] Jade!

280
00:16:00,833 --> 00:16:03,667
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

281
00:16:03,667 --> 00:16:05,500
- Justin.
- You're rude now?

282
00:16:06,833 --> 00:16:08,067
Why are you talking
to Mom like that?

283
00:16:10,533 --> 00:16:13,133
Why? It's true!

284
00:16:13,133 --> 00:16:15,733
Mom wasn't like this
when Dad was still alive!

285
00:16:17,700 --> 00:16:19,033
When it mattered.

286
00:16:20,800 --> 00:16:22,700
- Jade...
- I'll take care of this, Mom.

287
00:16:23,700 --> 00:16:24,967
She just wants to spend time
with you!

288
00:16:24,967 --> 00:16:26,367
You can't even accommodate that?

289
00:16:26,867 --> 00:16:28,100
Why are you acting like that?!

290
00:16:29,800 --> 00:16:32,467
Can't I say no?!

291
00:16:32,467 --> 00:16:33,700
Don't reason
that you're like that

292
00:16:33,700 --> 00:16:35,067
because you're grieving
over Dad.

293
00:16:35,067 --> 00:16:36,900
Mom is also grieving,
but she's not rude.

294
00:16:36,900 --> 00:16:38,867
- She's trying her best.
- [JADE] And it's too late!

295
00:16:38,867 --> 00:16:40,000
[JUSTIN] What's wrong with you?!

296
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:42,500
[FRIDA SCOFFS]

297
00:16:42,500 --> 00:16:43,700
You don't know anything.

298
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:46,933
- Are you crazy?!
- [LEON] What's with you?!

299
00:16:46,933 --> 00:16:49,567
- It's Jade!
- That's enough!

300
00:16:49,567 --> 00:16:50,733
Martin and the others
are waiting.

301
00:16:53,733 --> 00:16:59,500
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

302
00:16:59,500 --> 00:17:00,867
[LEON] Let's go!

303
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:05,067
[JUSTIN GRUNTS]

304
00:17:07,967 --> 00:17:14,900
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

305
00:17:28,800 --> 00:17:31,167
[MUSIC SWELLS]

306
00:17:32,600 --> 00:17:34,167
[LEON] You two have
to stop fighting.

307
00:17:34,167 --> 00:17:35,933
- [JUSTIN] Tell that to Jade!
- [JADE] Wow!

308
00:17:35,933 --> 00:17:37,500
[JUSTIN] There's something wrong
with her!

309
00:17:37,500 --> 00:17:38,767
- So it's me again?!
- Shut up!

310
00:17:38,767 --> 00:17:40,600
There's a voting
we have to deal with.

311
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:42,967
We're doing this for Dad.

312
00:17:44,600 --> 00:17:46,267
Uncle Michael murdered Dad.

313
00:17:46,267 --> 00:17:48,100
We should at least avenge him
through this.

314
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:52,600
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

315
00:17:52,633 --> 00:17:53,633
Right, Leon?

316
00:17:53,633 --> 00:18:00,600
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

317
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:09,200
[FOOTSTEPS]

318
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:16,133
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

319
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:38,167
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

320
00:18:44,700 --> 00:18:46,567
Good day to us all.

321
00:18:47,433 --> 00:18:48,700
How are you all doing?

322
00:18:50,667 --> 00:18:52,533
For those of you
who don't know me,

323
00:18:52,533 --> 00:18:54,667
I am Atty. Silvestre.

324
00:18:55,367 --> 00:18:57,633
And across me is
Atty. De Castro.

325
00:18:57,633 --> 00:19:01,367
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

326
00:19:01,367 --> 00:19:03,533
Let's get this started,
Attorney.

327
00:19:03,533 --> 00:19:04,833
So we could get it over with.

328
00:19:05,867 --> 00:19:08,567
[SILVESTRE] Okay.
So, let's get down to business.

329
00:19:09,400 --> 00:19:12,233
We are here today
to agree

330
00:19:12,233 --> 00:19:16,400
on who will be
the general manager of Hotel 88.

331
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:23,367
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

332
00:19:29,233 --> 00:19:31,567
[SILVESTRE] Two names
have been nominated

333
00:19:31,567 --> 00:19:32,867
for this position.

334
00:19:33,567 --> 00:19:36,467
First, Martin Madrigal.

335
00:19:37,433 --> 00:19:41,233
Who is one of the heirs
of Mr. Michael Fernandez.

336
00:19:41,767 --> 00:19:45,300
Second, Ms. Luna Almazan.

337
00:19:45,633 --> 00:19:50,233
One of the legal heirs
of Mr. Federico Almazan

338
00:19:53,300 --> 00:19:56,867
[SILVESTRE] It has been decided
to have our vote face-to- face.

339
00:20:00,767 --> 00:20:02,233
Let's start?

340
00:20:03,967 --> 00:20:05,633
Francis Endaya.

341
00:20:05,633 --> 00:20:10,433
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

342
00:20:10,433 --> 00:20:12,233
I vote for Martin.

343
00:20:13,667 --> 00:20:17,233
[SILVESTRE] One vote
for Mr. Madrigal.

344
00:20:22,333 --> 00:20:23,933
Ms. Jade Almazan.

345
00:20:28,700 --> 00:20:31,267
I vote for Luna.

346
00:20:34,367 --> 00:20:36,300
[SILVESTRE] One vote
for Mr. Madrigal,

347
00:20:36,333 --> 00:20:39,233
and one vote for Ms. Almazan.

348
00:20:39,233 --> 00:20:44,667
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

349
00:20:44,667 --> 00:20:46,667
Mr. Gio Cabrera.

350
00:20:50,733 --> 00:20:51,933
Martin.

351
00:20:54,633 --> 00:20:56,700
[SILVESTRE]
Two votes for Mr. Madrigal

352
00:20:56,700 --> 00:20:58,833
and one vote for Ms. Almazan.

353
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:01,767
Justin Almazan.

354
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:04,333
Of course,

355
00:21:04,967 --> 00:21:06,467
I vote for Luna.

356
00:21:07,533 --> 00:21:09,867
[SILVESTRE] So we have
two votes for Mr. Madrigal

357
00:21:09,900 --> 00:21:12,600
and two votes for
Ms. Almazan.

358
00:21:12,600 --> 00:21:14,733
- Martin Madrigal.
- Luna Almazan.

359
00:21:14,733 --> 00:21:21,667
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

360
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:24,500
Three votes for
Mr. Madrigal

361
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:26,833
and three votes for
Ms. Almazan.

362
00:21:28,533 --> 00:21:30,367
And so...

363
00:21:30,367 --> 00:21:32,367
Mr. Leon Almazan,

364
00:21:32,367 --> 00:21:34,533
Your vote will determine

365
00:21:34,533 --> 00:21:38,033
who will be
the general manager of Hotel 88.

366
00:21:38,033 --> 00:21:44,967
[STIRRING MUSING CONTINUES]

367
00:21:48,900 --> 00:21:50,367
[SILVESTRE] Mr. Leon.

368
00:22:06,767 --> 00:22:08,567
- [BIRDS CHIRPING]
- [PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

369
00:22:08,567 --> 00:22:10,233
Mr. Leon Almazan.

370
00:22:25,300 --> 00:22:32,267
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

371
00:22:34,300 --> 00:22:35,300
Luna.

372
00:22:40,433 --> 00:22:41,600
Luna Almazan.

373
00:22:41,600 --> 00:22:42,633
Yes!

374
00:22:42,633 --> 00:22:44,100
Woo-hoo!

375
00:22:44,600 --> 00:22:46,133
- Thank you, Leon.
- [JADE] Congratulations, Luna.

376
00:22:46,133 --> 00:22:47,267
[ATTY. SILVESTRE] Okay.

377
00:22:48,133 --> 00:22:50,967
So, we have three votes
for Mr. Madrigal,

378
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:53,100
and four votes for Ms. Almazan.

379
00:22:54,100 --> 00:22:57,200
Our general manager
for Hotel 88

380
00:22:57,200 --> 00:22:59,100
is Ms. Luna Almazan.

381
00:22:59,100 --> 00:23:00,633
Congratulations.

382
00:23:00,633 --> 00:23:01,500
Congratulations, Jade.

383
00:23:02,133 --> 00:23:04,100
[SNICKERS] I told you, guys.

384
00:23:04,100 --> 00:23:07,600
The new GM of Hotel 88, people!

385
00:23:07,600 --> 00:23:10,433
[SNICKERS]

386
00:23:10,433 --> 00:23:11,433
Oh.

387
00:23:11,433 --> 00:23:18,400
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

388
00:23:33,467 --> 00:23:37,333
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

389
00:23:38,367 --> 00:23:40,500
<i> Luna going to be our boss?</i>

390
00:23:40,500 --> 00:23:42,500
Housekeeping or security guard?

391
00:23:42,500 --> 00:23:44,300
<i>What the hell
is wrong with you?!</i>

392
00:23:44,300 --> 00:23:45,300
<i> Is that Leon?</i>

393
00:23:45,300 --> 00:23:47,233
<i> I don't want us
to resent each other.</i>

394
00:23:47,233 --> 00:23:48,900
<i> Blood is thicker than water.</i>

395
00:23:48,900 --> 00:23:51,167
<i>- E-Edward--
- You chose Edward to promote?</i>

396
00:23:53,967 --> 00:23:55,633
<i>I have to tilt the power
back to us.</i>

397
00:23:55,667 --> 00:23:56,733
<i> Are you crazy, Bok?</i>

398
00:23:56,733 --> 00:23:58,500
<i> I told you I'll pay you,
didn't I?</i>

399
00:23:58,500 --> 00:23:59,567
<i> Hurry up, Gio.</i>

400
00:23:59,567 --> 00:24:02,000
<i> Don't wait for me
to go back to your grandma.</i>

